    "Retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) has been proposed as a new framework for AI that seeks to integrate additional knowledge, such as organizational data, and generate results that can be linked to that knowledge (Lewis et al. 2020).",
    "This allows users to access information from within an organization and reduces the risk of hallucinations.",
    "This new architecture offers important advancements compared to previous architectures and presents new challenges for research and academia.",
    "Previous catchword articles have already covered important aspects of AI, namely fair AI (Feuerriegel et al. 2020), AI as a Service (Lins et al. 2021), foundation models (Schneider et al. 2024), and generative AI (Feuerriegel et al. 2024).",
    "We contribute to this ongoing engagement with current AI developments by focusing on RAG."
